executeFirstBest

public int executeFirstBest(NodesLinkedList mainNodes)
Performs local three forward interchange for the route. Each successive triplet of point cells are removed and inserted after each of the point cells after them. The point cell triplet is selected in order from the first to the last. If the new route is feasible and the new cost is better than the original cost, then the new route is saved. If at the end of the interchange there has been a new best cost route, then the permanent changes are made. This local interchange will run until no changes are being made to the route. Ex: D1<-->P1<-->P2<-->P3<-->P4<-->P5<-->D2 D1<-->P4<-->P1<-->P2<-->P3<-->P5<-->D2 D1<-->P4<-->P5<-->P1<-->P2<-->P3<-->D2

Specified by:
executeFirstBest in class IntraOptimization
Parameters:
mainNodes - the route to perform the optimizations on
Returns:
number of changes
